(15,'adarsh-pathange','Senior Systems Engineer','Infosys','1','1','2020','30','11','2021','> Led database design, implementation, and migration projects, ensuring smooth transition and minimal disruption to business operations.\n> Leveraged T-SQL programming and database optimization expertise to design and implement highly performant databases with optimized indexing strategies and maintenance plans.\n> Designed and implemented high availability and replication solutions, such as Always On and Clustering, ensuring maximum system availability and minimizing risk of data loss.\n> Mentored and coached junior team members, fostering a positive and productive work environment, resulting in enhanced team collaboration and individual growth.\n> Streamlined daily refreshes by automating critical operations, resulting in a 60% reduction in workload and reduced manpower.\n> Utilized extensive tools, such as Delphix, SolarWinds, RedGate, ServiceNow, and Attunity, to perform critical operations, including performance tuning, monitoring, and refreshes.\n> Successfully migrated 20+ servers from On-Premise to Azure VM (IAAS) cloud independently, ensuring seamless replication of data and zero downtime.\n> Received high recognition and appreciation from clients for exceptional work, quality deliverables, and effective communication.\n> Developed and implemented robust backup and recovery strategies, database security protocols, and disaster recovery plans to minimize risk and maintain data integrity.\n> Delivered full life cycle support for SQL server and database management, including conducting assessments, installations, creations, decommissions, and migrations.\n> Led by example, setting high standards for performance, ethics, and professionalism.','https://www.linkedin.com/company/infosys'),
